PREFACE.

THE task of preparing for the press this edition of Theodore of Mopsuestia’s newly recovered commentary upon the minor Epistles of S. Paul was taken in hand early in the year 1875. Its completion has been delayed partly by the laborious and intricate nature os the work, partly by unforeseen circumstances which brought upon me abundant occupation of another kind. As a foreign edition which was designed to embrace the greater part os the commentary had been discontinued on the under- standing that the present work would shortly be ready for publication, it was thought right to issue the first volume at once. The second volume, if I am permitted to finish it, will follow in the course of another year, and will contain‚ besides the remainder of the commentary, an appendix and indiceS.
